snippet: Even as conservatives celebrated coming out on the winning side of a divisive social issue, their court victory may have also handed Democrats an issue that will turn out liberal voters.
abstract: News analysis; Supreme Court's ruling that government cannot force certain employers to pay for birth control is one that both conservatives and liberals can run with; even as conservatives celebrate coming out on winning side of divisive social issue, their court victory may have also handed Democrats an issue that will turn out liberal voters in fall mid-term elections.

byline.original: By JEREMY W. PETERS and MICHAEL D. SHEAR

lead_paragraph: Even as conservatives celebrated coming out on the winning side of a divisive social issue, their court victory may have also handed Democrats an issue that will turn out liberal voters.

headline.seo: Hobby Lobby Decision Highlights Parties’ Divide
headline.main: A Ruling That Both Sides Can Run With
